rComments: Tom is great! Really nice, and really helpful outside of class. I wasn't a huge fan of the in-class assignments, but that's really the only thing I had a problem with.

In my 2 years at UTSC, I have learned more from Professor Tom's courses than anyone else's. I took a course with him once before and jumped to take another one this summer, even though Dystopian Lit. is not my genre. He wants all his students to excel and is always pushing them to seek his help out, even if the essay is due in an hour! Best Prof!

Dr. Ue was such a great professor. He's a little intimidating at first, but when you get to know him, he's hilarious and extremely helpful. Definitely recommend going to office hours/emailing him questions. Don't stress about assignments; he takes time to make sure they're clear. Attend every lecture and get ready to discuss texts.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']
